text:
first-time macbook user thoughts (<1  week):
- learning new hotkeys is hard work after being exclusively a windows-only user
- changing caps lock to work as a command key was an elite suggestion (ty @sdv.eth)
- removing dock hide delay was also an elite suggestion (ty again @sdv.eth)
- i love that i can share my internet with my phone via usb (great for weak wi-fi areas where phone seems to drop in and out)
- mission control, app expose and hot corners are actually awesome once you can accept a new way of navigating round your desktop space (not using the taskbar / alt tab like windows)
- battery life is ACTUALLY insane, now i see why everyone wanders around with a macbook and no charger

wants:
- i want to be able to two-finger swipe back and forward on warpcast like i can on twitter and other websites
- an equivalent of ninite for macOS
- more power-user suggestions pls
